aiobungie.crate

Basic implementations of aiobungie client crates.

These crates are used to organize the flow and how things stracture for functional usage for the Bungie API objects.

@attrs.define(kw_only=True)
class Activity:
View Source 
554@attrs.define(kw_only=True)
555class Activity:
556    """Represents a Bungie Activity."""
557
558    net: traits.Netrunner = attrs.field(repr=False, hash=False, eq=False)
559    """A network state used for making external requests."""
560
561    hash: int
562    """The activity's reference id or hash."""
563
564    membership_type: enums.MembershipType
565    """The activity player's membership type."""
566
567    instance_id: int
568    """The activity's instance id."""
569
570    mode: enums.GameMode
571    """The activity mode or type."""
572
573    modes: collections.Sequence[enums.GameMode]
574    """Sequence of the activity's gamemodes."""
575
576    is_private: bool
577    """Whether this activity is private or not."""
578
579    occurred_at: datetime.datetime
580    """A datetime of when did this activity occurred."""
581
582    values: ActivityValues
583    """Information occurred in this activity."""
584
585    @property
586    def is_flawless(self) -> bool:
587        """Whether this activity was a flawless run or not."""
588        return self.values.deaths == 0 and self.values.is_completed is True
589
590    @property
591    def is_solo(self) -> bool:
592        """Whether this activity was completed solo or not."""
593        return self.values.player_count == 1 and self.values.is_completed
594
595    @property
596    def is_solo_flawless(self) -> bool:
597        """Whether this activity was completed solo and flawless."""
598        return self.is_solo & self.is_flawless
599
600    @property
601    def reference_id(self) -> int:
602        """An alias to the activity's hash"""
603        return self.hash
604
605    async def fetch_post(self) -> PostActivity:
606        """Fetch this activity's data after it was finished.
607
608        Returns
609        -------
610        `PostActivity`
611            A post activity object.
612        """
613        return await self.net.request.fetch_post_activity(self.instance_id)
614
615    def __int__(self) -> int:
616        return self.instance_id

421    async def edit_options(
422        self,
423        access_token: str,
424        /,
425        *,
426        invite_permissions_override: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
427        update_culture_permissionOverride: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
428        host_guided_game_permission_override: typedefs.NoneOr[
429            typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]
430        ] = None,
431        update_banner_permission_override: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
432        join_level: typedefs.NoneOr[typedefs.IntAnd[enums.ClanMemberType]] = None,
433    ) -> None:
434        """Edit this clan's options.
435
436        Notes
437        -----
438        * This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: `AdminGroups` scope.
439        * All arguments will be ignored if set to `None`. This does not include `access_token`
440
441        Parameters
442        ----------
443        access_token : `builtins.str`
444            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
445
446        Other Parameters
447        ----------------
448        invite_permissions_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
449            Minimum Member Level allowed to invite new members to group
450            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
451            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
452            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
453        update_culture_permissionOverride : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
454            Minimum Member Level allowed to update group culture
455            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
456            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
457            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
458        host_guided_game_permission_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
459            Minimum Member Level allowed to host guided games
460            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder, Admin
461            Allowed Overrides: `0` -> None, `1` -> Beginner `2` -> Member.
462            Default is Member for clans, None for groups, although this means nothing for groups.
463        update_banner_permission_override : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
464            Minimum Member Level allowed to update banner
465            Always Allowed: Founder, Acting Founder
466            True means admins have this power, false means they don't
467            Default is False for clans, True for groups.
468        join_level : `aiobungie.ClanMemberType`
469            Level to join a member at when accepting an invite, application, or joining an open clan.
470            Default is `aiobungie.ClanMemberType.BEGINNER`
471        """
472        await self.net.request.rest.edit_clan_options(
473            access_token,
474            group_id=self.id,
475            invite_permissions_override=invite_permissions_override,
476            update_culture_permissionOverride=update_culture_permissionOverride,
477            host_guided_game_permission_override=host_guided_game_permission_override,
478            update_banner_permission_override=update_banner_permission_override,
479            join_level=join_level,
480        )

482    async def edit(
483        self,
484        access_token: str,
485        /,
486        *,
487        name: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
488        about: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
489        motto: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
490        theme: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
491        tags: typedefs.NoneOr[collections.Sequence[str]] = None,
492        is_public: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
493        locale: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
494        avatar_image_index: typedefs.NoneOr[int] = None,
495        membership_option: typedefs.NoneOr[
496            typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipOption]
497        ] = None,
498        allow_chat: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
499        chat_security: typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1]] = None,
500        call_sign: typedefs.NoneOr[str] = None,
501        homepage: typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]] = None,
502        enable_invite_messaging_for_admins: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
503        default_publicity: typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]] = None,
504        is_public_topic_admin: typedefs.NoneOr[bool] = None,
505    ) -> None:
506        """Edit this clan.
507
508        Notes
509        -----
510        * This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: `AdminGroups` scope.
511        * All arguments will default to `None` if not provided. This does not include `access_token` and `group_id`
512
513        Parameters
514        ----------
515        access_token : `str`
516            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
517
518        Other Parameters
519        ----------------
520        name : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
521            The name to edit the clan with.
522        about : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
523            The about section to edit the clan with.
524        motto : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
525            The motto section to edit the clan with.
526        theme : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
527            The theme name to edit the clan with.
528        tags : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[collections.Sequence[str]]`
529            A sequence of strings to replace the clan tags with.
530        is_public : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
531            If provided and set to `True`, The clan will set to private.
532            If provided and set to `False`, The clan will set to public whether it was or not.
533        locale : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
534            The locale section to edit the clan with.
535        avatar_image_index : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[int]`
536            The clan avatar image index to edit the clan with.
537        membership_option : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipOption]]` # noqa: E501 # Line too long
538            The clan membership option to edit it with.
539        allow_chat : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
540            If provided and set to `True`, The clan members will be allowed to chat.
541            If provided and set to `False`, The clan members will not be allowed to chat.
542        chat_security : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1]]`
543            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat security will be edited to `Group` only.
544            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat security will be edited to `Admin` only.
545        call_sign : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]`
546            The clan call sign to edit it with.
547        homepage : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
548            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `Wall`.
549            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `Forum`.
550            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat homepage will be edited to `AllianceForum`.
551        enable_invite_messaging_for_admins : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
552            ???
553        default_publicity : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1, 2]]`
554            If provided and set to `0`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Public`.
555            If provided and set to `1`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Alliance`.
556            If provided and set to `2`, The clan chat publicity will be edited to `Private`.
557        is_public_topic_admin : `aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]`
558            ???
559        """
560        await self.net.request.rest.edit_clan(
561            access_token,
562            group_id=self.id,
563            name=name,
564            about=about,
565            motto=motto,
566            theme=theme,
567            tags=tags,
568            is_public=is_public,
569            locale=locale,
570            avatar_image_index=avatar_image_index,
571            membership_option=membership_option,
572            allow_chat=allow_chat,
573            chat_security=chat_security,
574            call_sign=call_sign,
575            homepage=homepage,
576            enable_invite_messaging_for_admins=enable_invite_messaging_for_admins,
577            default_publicity=default_publicity,
578            is_public_topic_admin=is_public_topic_admin,
579        )

581    async def fetch_avaliable_fireteams(
582        self,
583        access_token: str,
584        activity_type: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamActivity],
585        *,
586        platform: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamPlatform],
587        language: typing.Union[fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str],
588        date_range: typedefs.IntAnd[
589            fireteams.FireteamDate
590        ] = fireteams.FireteamDate.ALL,
591        page: int = 0,
592        public_only: bool = False,
593        slots_filter: int = 0,
594    ) -> typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[fireteams.Fireteam]]:
595        """Fetch a clan's fireteams with open slots.
596
597        .. note::
598            This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.
599
600        Parameters
601        ----------
602        access_token : `str`
603            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
604        activity_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.FireteamActivity]`
605            The fireteam activity type.
606
607        Other Parameters
608        ----------------
609        platform : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamPlatform]`
610            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
611            Defaults to `aiobungie.crate.FireteamPlatform.ANY` which returns all platforms.
612        language : `typing.Union[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str]`
613            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
614            Defaults to `aiobungie.crate.FireteamLanguage.ALL`
615        date_range : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.FireteamDate]`
616            An integer to filter the date range of the returned fireteams. Defaults to `aiobungie.FireteamDate.ALL`.
617        page : `int`
618            The page number. By default its `0` which returns all available activities.
619        public_only: `bool`
620            If set to True, Then only public fireteams will be returned.
621        slots_filter : `int`
622            Filter the returned fireteams based on available slots. Default is `0`
623        """
624        fireteams_ = await self.net.request.fetch_avaliable_clan_fireteams(
625            access_token,
626            self.id,
627            activity_type,
628            platform=platform,
629            language=language,
630            date_range=date_range,
631            page=page,
632            public_only=public_only,
633            slots_filter=slots_filter,
634        )
635        if fireteams_ is None:
636            return None
637        assert isinstance(fireteams_, list)
638        return fireteams_

640    async def fetch_fireteams(
641        self,
642        access_token: str,
643        *,
644        include_closed: bool = True,
645        platform: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamPlatform],
646        language: typing.Union[fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str],
647        filtered: bool = True,
648        page: int = 0,
649    ) -> collections.Sequence[fireteams.AvailableFireteam]:
650        """Fetch this clan's available fireteams.
651
652        .. note::
653            This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.
654
655        Parameters
656        ----------
657        access_token : str
658            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
659
660        Other Parameters
661        ----------------
662        include_closed : bool
663            If provided and set to True, It will also return closed fireteams.
664            If provided and set to False, It will only return public fireteams. Default is True.
665        platform : aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamPlatform]
666            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
667            Defaults to aiobungie.crate.FireteamPlatform.ANY which returns all platforms.
668        language : typing.Union[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str]
669            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
670            Defaults to aiobungie.crate.FireteamLanguage.ALL
671        filtered : bool
672            If set to True, it will filter by clan. Otherwise not. Default is True.
673        page : int
674            The page number. By default its 0 which returns all available activities.
675
676        Returns
677        -------
678        `typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crate.AvalaibleFireteam]]`
679            A sequence of available fireteams objects if exists. else `None` will be returned.
680        """
681        fireteams_ = await self.net.request.fetch_my_clan_fireteams(
682            access_token,
683            self.id,
684            include_closed=include_closed,
685            platform=platform,
686            language=language,
687            filtered=filtered,
688            page=page,
689        )
690        assert isinstance(fireteams, list)
691        return fireteams_

@attrs.define(kw_only=True)
class Component(aiobungie.crate.ProfileComponent, aiobungie.crate.RecordsComponent, aiobungie.crate.StringVariableComponent, aiobungie.crate.components.MetricsComponent):
View Source 
487@attrs.define(kw_only=True)
488class Component(
489    ProfileComponent, RecordsComponent, StringVariableComponent, MetricsComponent
490):
491    """Concerete implementation of all Bungie components.
492
493    Components that requires auth will return `None` unless an `access_token` was passed to the request
494    `**options` parameters.
495
496    Example
497    -------
498    ```py
499    import aiobungie
500
501    # The components to get and return.
502    components = [
503        aiobungie.ComponentType.PROFILE,
504        aiobungie.ComponentType.CHARACTERS,
505        aiobungie.ComponentType.PROFILE_INVENTORIES,
506    ]
507    profile = await client.fetch_profile(
508        id,
509        aiobungie.MembershipType.STEAM,
510        components,
511        # Assuming the component requires an auth token
512        auth="Some Bearer access token"
513    )
514    if items := profile.profile_inventories:
515        for item in items:
516            if item.hash == 1946491241:
517                print(await item.fetch_self())
518    ```
519
520    Included Components
521    -------------------
522    - All
523    """
524
525    characters: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, character_.Character]]
526    """A mapping from character's id to`aiobungie.crate.Character`
527    of the associated character within the character component.
528
529    This will be available when `aiobungie.ComponentType.CHARACTERS` is passed to the request.
530    otherwise will be `None`.
531    """
532
533    character_inventories: typing.Optional[
534        collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]]
535    ]
536    """A mapping from character's id to a sequence of their character inventorie items component.

Concerete implementation of all Bungie components.

Components that requires auth will return None unless an access_token was passed to the request **options parameters.

Example
import aiobungie

# The components to get and return.
components = [
    aiobungie.ComponentType.PROFILE,
    aiobungie.ComponentType.CHARACTERS,
    aiobungie.ComponentType.PROFILE_INVENTORIES,
]
profile = await client.fetch_profile(
    id,
    aiobungie.MembershipType.STEAM,
    components,
    # Assuming the component requires an auth token
    auth="Some Bearer access token"
)
if items := profile.profile_inventories:
    for item in items:
        if item.hash == 1946491241:
            print(await item.fetch_self())

121@attrs.define(kw_only=True)
122class CraftablesComponent:
123    """Represents craftables-only Bungie component."""

125    net: traits.Netrunner = attrs.field(repr=False, eq=False, hash=False)
126    """A network state used for making external requests."""

128    craftables: collections.Mapping[int, typing.Optional[items.CraftableItem]]
129    """A mapping from craftable item IDs to a craftable item component.
130
131    Items may or may not be available but its hash will always be available.
132    You can use the hash to fetch those items using `fetch_craftables` method.
133    """
134
135    crafting_root_node_hash: int
136    """The hash for the root presentation node definition of craftable item categories."""
137
138    async def fetch_craftables(
139        self, limit: typing.Optional[int] = None
140    ) -> typing.Optional[collections.Collection[entity.InventoryEntity]]:
141        """Fetch the inventory definitions for the craftables.
142
143        Parameters
144        ----------
145        limit : `typing.Optional[int]`
146            The maximum number of items to fetch. If not provided, all items will be fetched.
147
148        Returns
149        -------
150        `typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[entity.InventoryEntity]]`
151            If the craftables are available, a sequence of inventory entities. Otherwise `None`.
152        """
153
154        if self.craftables is None:
155            return None
156
157        item_ids = list(self.craftables.keys())
158        return await helpers.awaits(
159            *[
160                self.net.request.fetch_inventory_item(item_id)
161                for item_id in item_ids[:limit]
162            ],
163        )

Represents craftables-only Bungie component.

289    async def fetch_self_profile(
290        self, components: list[enums.ComponentType], auth: typing.Optional[str] = None
291    ) -> components_.Component:
292        """Fetch this user's profile.
293
294        Parameters
295        ----------
296        components : `list[aiobungie.ComponentType]`
297            A list of profile components to collect and return.
298            This either can be arguments of integers or `aiobungie.ComponentType`.
299
300        Other Parameters
301        ----------------
302        auth : `typing.Optional[str]`
303            A Bearer access_token to make the request with.
304            This is optional and limited to components that only requires an Authorization token.
305
306        Returns
307        --------
308        `aiobungie.crate.Component`
309            A Destiny 2 player profile with its components.
310            Only passed components will be available if they exists. Otherwise they will be `None`
311        """
312        profile_ = await self.net.request.fetch_profile(
313            self.id, self.type, components, auth
314        )
315        assert isinstance(profile_, components_.Component)
316        return profile_
